cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is about image super-resolution using generative adversarial networks and perceptual metrics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel loss function to optimize perceptual quality, which involves training a ranker to learn the behavior of perceptual metrics. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper includes experiments and comparisons with other super-resolution methods, which may indicate that it belongs to the graphics sub-category (cs.GR).
